511→    /**
512→     * Delayed task queue maintains stable time-comparision invariant despite potential wraparounds in
513→     * long nano time measurements by maintaining last observed [timeNow]. It protects the integrity of the
514→     * heap data structure in spite of potential non-monotonicity of `nanoTime()` source.
515→     * The invariant is that for every scheduled [DelayedTask]:
516→     *
517→     * ```
518→     * delayedTask.nanoTime - timeNow >= 0
519→     * ```
520→     *
521→     * So the comparison of scheduled tasks via [DelayedTask.compareTo] is always stable as
522→     * scheduled [DelayedTask.nanoTime] can be at most [Long.MAX_VALUE] apart. This invariant is maintained when
523→     * new tasks are added by [DelayedTask.scheduleTask] function and it cannot be violated when tasks are removed
524→     * (so there is nothing special to do there).
525→     */
526→    internal class DelayedTaskQueue(
527→        @JvmField var timeNow: Long
528→    ) : ThreadSafeHeap<DelayedTask>()
529→}
